<section xml:id="IN7" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Graphing with derivatives (IN7)</title>
  <objectives>
    <ul>
      <li>
          <xi:include href="outcomes/07.ptx" /></li>
      
    </ul>
  </objectives>

    <p>In <xref ref="IN5"/> and <xref ref="IN6"/> we learned how the first and second derivatives give us information about the graph of a function. Specifically, we can determine the intervals where a function is increasing, decreasing, concave up, or concave down as well as any relative extrema or inflection points. Now we will put that information together to draw a sketch of the graph.
        </p>
    
